  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <pb n="1" facs="#p1" />
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_3" />
        <ab>God.asdasdas</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_5" />
        <ab>Gods.</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_6" />
        <ab>Sacred book called Monas or the eighth book of <persName
                    >Moses</persName><note
                    >Moses is traditionally considered the author of magical texts in the PGM corpus.</note></ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_7" />
        <ab>Concerning the holy <choice><abbr>name</abbr><expan
                        >name (ὄνομα)</expan></choice>, it contains thus: remain pure</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_8" />
        <ab>for <num
                        type="cardinal"
                        value="41"
                    >forty-one</num> days, having <choice><sic
                        >whispered</sic><corr
                        >prophesied</corr></choice>, so that you may arrive at the conjunction in</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_9" />
        <ab><placeName>Aries</placeName>. Have a level house, where before</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_10" />
        <ab>no one died. Let the door face</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_11" />
        <ab
                >west, and having erected in the middle of the house an earthen altar</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_12" />
        <ab>and cypress wood, right-twisted cones, ten cocks</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_13" />
        <ab>two white, uninjured, perfect, and two lamps</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_15" />
        <ab>quarter-sized, having <choice><sic>filled</sic><corr
                        >filled</corr></choice> with good oil, and no longer</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_16" />
        <ab>pour in after entering. For the <rs
                        type="divine"
                    >god</rs> will be exalted more</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_17" />
        <ab>Let the table be supplied with these incense offerings</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_18" />
        <ab>which are congenial to the <rs
                        type="divine"
                    >god</rs>. From this</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_19" />
        <ab>book <persName
                    >Hermes</persName>, having stolen the incense offerings, invoked</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_21" />
        <ab>his own sacred book, called Wing: for</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_22" />
        <ab><persName
                    >Kronos</persName>, styrax, for it is heavy and fragrant; for <persName
                    >Zeus</persName></ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_23" />
        <ab>malabathrum; for <persName>Ares</persName>, costus; for <persName
                    >Helios</persName>, frankincense</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_24" />
        <ab>for <persName>Aphrodite</persName>, Indian nard; for <persName
                    >Hermes</persName>, cassia</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_25" />
        <ab>for the <rs
                        type="astral"
                    >Moon</rs>, myrrh. These are the secret incense offerings</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_27" />
        <ab>What it says in the Key of <persName
                    >Moses</persName>: preparations for every</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_28" />
        <ab>vetch, solar, Egyptian bean. With these it says:</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_29" />
        <ab>And these <persName
                    >Manetho</persName> said in his own book. From here</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_30" />
        <ab>taking the <num
                        type="cardinal"
                        value="7"
                    >seven</num> flowers of the <num
                        type="cardinal"
                        value="7"
                    >seven</num> stars which are: marjoram</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_31" />
        <ab>common garden, lotus, ivy leaf, narcissus</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_33" />
        <ab>lily, rose. These flowers before twenty</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_34" />
        <ab>one days before the rite, grind finely to white</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_35" />
        <ab>incense and dry in shade and have them ready for</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_36" />
        <ab>that day. But first establish friendship</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_37" />
        <ab>at any new moon according to the <rs
                        type="divine"
                    >god</rs> of the horoscope</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_39" />
        <ab>gods, which you have in the Key. You will be initiated to them</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_40" />
        <ab>thus: make from fine flour <num
                        type="cardinal"
                        value="3"
                    >three</num> zodiac signs: bull-faced</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_41" />
        <ab><choice><abbr>figure</abbr><expan
                        >figure (πρόσωπον)</expan></choice>, goat-faced <choice
                    ><abbr>figure</abbr><expan
                        >figure (πρόσωπον)</expan></choice>, ram-faced figure, each of them</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_42" />
        <ab>standing at the pole holding Egyptian whips, and</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_43" />
        <ab>having fumigated, consume speaking the horoscope</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_45" />
        <ab
                >formula in the Key and the compelling formula and the hebdomadal</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_46" />
        <ab>appointed ones, and you will be initiated to them</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_47" />
        <ab>Then for the universal constitution, have square natron</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_48" />
        <ab>on which you write the great <choice><abbr>name</abbr><expan
                        >name (ὄνομα)</expan></choice> with the seven vowels. Instead of</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_49" />
        <ab>the hissing and whistling, write on one side</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_51" />
        <ab>of the natron a crocodile, falcon-headed, and above it standing</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_52" />
        <ab>the nine-formed. For he himself, the falcon-headed</ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_53" />
        <ab>crocodile, at the <num
                        type="cardinal"
                        value="4"
                    >four</num> turnings greets the <rs
                        type="divine"
                    >god</rs></ab>
        <lb facs="#z_tr_1_tl_54" />
        <ab>with hissing. For having breathed, it hisses from the depths</ab>
      </div>
